## Difference Between DFS Traversals

| Traversal | Order               |
| --------- | ------------------- |
| Preorder  | Node → Left → Right |
| Inorder   | Left → Node → Right |
| Postorder | Left → Right → Node |

The only difference is **where the current node is visited**.

---

## Takeaway

The key idea of Inorder Traversal is to **completely process the left subtree before visiting the current node**, and then process the right subtree. This recursive **Left → Node → Right** pattern visits every node exactly once and is especially important because **it returns the nodes in sorted order for a Binary Search Tree (BST)**.
